<title type="html"><![CDATA[9/1(Thu) Education vs. Experience / you could live to a hundred (Host: Larry)]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/viewtopic.php?t=648&amp;p=673#p673"><![CDATA[
9/1(Thu) Education Vs Experience / you could live to a hundred (Host: Larry)<br /><br />Agenda:<br />7:00-7:05 pm Opening Remarks<br />7:05-7:40 pm Session 1: Group Discussion<br />7:40-8:00 pm Individual Presentation<br />8:00-8:05 pm Break<br />8:05-8:40: Session 2: Group Discussion<br />8:40-9:00 pm Individual Presentation<br /><br />We will hold a zoom meeting only.<br /><br />Zoom meeting: Please click the link below<br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://zoomtw.zoom.us/j/92987266213?pw">https://zoomtw.zoom.us/j/92987266213?pw</a><!-- m --> ...<br />Meeting ID:929 8726 6213<br />Password:112233<br /><br />Session I<br />Education vs. Experience--Which is more important?<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.hubrecruiting.com/blog/education-vs-experience-which-is-more-important">https://www.hubrecruiting.com/blog/educ ... -important</a><!-- m --><br /><br />Questions:<br /><br />1. Based on your work experience, do you think experience<br />and education which one is more important? Why?<br />2. Many people continue on the job training to obtain higher education after working for some time. Do you know what is the purpose? What are the benefits of these degrees?<br />3. Do you think Taiwan education is really helpful for you to find a job or work? Why?<br />4. At present, high education in Taiwan is becoming and more easily get. Do you think this is a good thing or a bad thing and why? Would you go for a higher degree if given the chance and why?<br /><br />----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br /><br />Session II<br />6 signs that you could live to a hundred<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://longevity.technology/lifestyle/6-signs-that-you-could-live-to-a-hundred/">https://longevity.technology/lifestyle/ ... a-hundred/</a><!-- m --><br /><br />Questions:<br /><br />1. Do you agree with the statement that as long as you meet the six signs in the article mentioned, you can live to 100 years old? Or not and why?<br />2. Do you know what signs people probably die young? Why?<br />3. According to statistics, the average life expectancy in Taipei is 84 years old, and in Taitung is 76.6 years old. Do you know why the life expectancy of living in the countryside is relatively short? and living in big city Taipei for long? why?<br />4. Do you think which one is the most important to live a meaningful life, a healthy life, or a long life for you, and why?<br /><br /><br />P.S.<br />1.參加三次(含實體及線上會議)後，只要繳交1,000元(學生500元)，即可成為ROYAL終身會員!<br />2.請帶著開放的心與熱情來參加全英文會話聚會!<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=38674">Louie Wang</a> — Sat Aug 27, 2022 5:48 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
